Key Match Events: Jaime Jaquez Jr. posted an efficient near triple-double statline in the game against Utah Jazz.
Miami outscored Utah by 4 points in Jaquez's 36 minutes, the highest among all starters.
Jaquez went 3 of 5 from 3-point range and stepped up for some clutch ones in the final minutes of the fourth quarter.
Post-Match Reflections: Jaime Jaquez Jr. expressed pride in his team's effort and his own performance, especially making crucial free throws down the stretch.
